cps.server

Class ServerController

  • java.lang.Object
    • cps.server.ServerController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RequestHandler<SessionHolder>

    public class ServerController
extends java.lang.Object
implements RequestHandler<SessionHolder>
    Main controller for server logic. Task: given a client request, perform the necessary actions (by delegating to specific controllers) and return a response object that will be sent back to the client. Client requests coming from customers are symbolically referred to as "Requests" and requests coming from Employees or Global Manager are referred to as "Service Actions". Each type of action that can be taken by the user in the client application is associated with a particular Request or ServiceAction class. Each of these classes has a handler defined in one of the specific controllers, and the job of this controller is to route each request to the appropriate handler and return the response.
